gates of the night ( french : les portes de la nuit ) is a 1946 french film that was directed by marcel carné . it starred serge reggiani and yves montand . the script was written by carné 's long-time collaborator jacques prévert . the film made its debut in the united states four years after its official release in france . it introduced the &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; popular song " autumn leaves " ( french : les &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; ) .